1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:02,670
Joseph: Everyone, hold on!

2
00:00:02,703 --> 00:00:05,005
Yaah!

3
00:00:05,038 --> 00:00:07,674
Oh, no!

4
00:00:10,077 --> 00:00:12,046
- ( Men groaning )
- ( Iggy snoring )

5
00:00:19,319 --> 00:00:21,621
Avdol: It sunk into the sand.
We should all be all right

6
00:00:21,655 --> 00:00:25,325
as long as we don’t move
and don’t make a sound.

7
00:00:26,326 --> 00:00:28,028
( N’doul chuckles )

8
00:00:28,061 --> 00:00:31,698
It’s much too late to try
hiding from me at this point.

9
00:00:31,732 --> 00:00:35,336
I know where each of you landed.
There’s no escaping now.

10
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:37,037
( Footstep echoes )

11
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:39,039
♪

12
00:00:51,752 --> 00:00:54,722
Four--no, five steps.

13
00:00:54,755 --> 00:00:58,559
I get it. You’re walking
quietly to avoid detection.

14
00:00:58,592 --> 00:01:01,328
But you can’t hide from me.

15
00:01:01,361 --> 00:01:03,096
Avdol: Tsk, tsk.

16
00:01:03,130 --> 00:01:06,367
It appears these "steps"
have thrown him for a loop.

17
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,369
Go ahead,
you accursed water stand.

18
00:01:08,402 --> 00:01:10,104
Just try to attack us,

19
00:01:10,137 --> 00:01:12,072
because the moment
you reveal yourself,

20
00:01:12,105 --> 00:01:15,308
i’ll vaporize you with the power
of my magician’s red.

21
00:01:23,717 --> 00:01:25,719
♪

22
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:29,756
( Singing in Japanese )

23
00:01:48,342 --> 00:01:50,344
♪

24
00:01:53,013 --> 00:01:54,715
- ( Soft scraping )
- Avdol: He’s here.

25
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:58,519
♪

26
00:01:58,552 --> 00:02:00,554
N’doul: Hold on. What’s this?

27
00:02:00,587 --> 00:02:02,556
He only moved
five steps forward.

28
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:05,192
How strange.

29
00:02:05,225 --> 00:02:06,993
Why has he suddenly
stopped moving?

30
00:02:09,396 --> 00:02:10,664
Now!

31
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:14,401
Magician’s red!

32
00:02:17,104 --> 00:02:18,138
What?!

33
00:02:19,373 --> 00:02:22,610
- ( All gasping )
- Joseph: Avdol!

34
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:25,545
( Iggy grunts )

35
00:02:27,548 --> 00:02:28,682
( Avdol groans )

36
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:30,383
How can he be so--

37
00:02:30,417 --> 00:02:31,385
( gasps )

38
00:02:31,418 --> 00:02:33,453
So quick?

39
00:02:33,487 --> 00:02:35,322
Polnareff: Avdol!

40
00:02:35,355 --> 00:02:37,257
( N’doul sighs )
I have to admit

41
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:39,960
that plan was actually
a stroke of brilliance.

42
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:43,330
I have to pay more attention
to their vibrations from now on.

43
00:02:44,398 --> 00:02:46,066
Those weren’t footsteps at all.

44
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:48,635
It would seem as though he threw
some kind of metal rings.

45
00:02:48,669 --> 00:02:50,671
And judging by these burns...

46
00:02:50,704 --> 00:02:53,740
( Chuckles )
I’d say avdol did the deed.

47
00:02:53,774 --> 00:02:55,242
( Avdol gasping )

48
00:02:55,275 --> 00:02:57,344
N’doul: But c’est la vie.

49
00:03:00,447 --> 00:03:01,648
Farewell...

50
00:03:01,682 --> 00:03:04,218
♪

51
00:03:04,251 --> 00:03:06,687
Avdol.

52
00:03:08,422 --> 00:03:10,291
Hmm? What’s this?

53
00:03:10,324 --> 00:03:11,559
Someone started running.

54
00:03:11,592 --> 00:03:13,227
Joseph: Jotaro,
what are you doing?!

55
00:03:13,260 --> 00:03:15,329
You know we can’t
just run around!

56
00:03:16,964 --> 00:03:19,366
N’doul: His stride
says he’s about 190--

57
00:03:19,399 --> 00:03:22,602
no, 195 centimeters tall.

58
00:03:22,636 --> 00:03:24,605
There’s a youthfulness
in his stride,

59
00:03:24,638 --> 00:03:26,273
so he’s not Joseph.

60
00:03:26,306 --> 00:03:29,743
It must be jotaro then,
but where exactly is he going?

61
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:32,612
( Polnareff gasps ) It dove in!

62
00:03:32,646 --> 00:03:34,348
I think it’s going after jotaro!

63
00:03:34,381 --> 00:03:36,116
Joseph: This can’t be happening!

64
00:03:36,149 --> 00:03:39,452
I’m grateful he’s not
attacking avdol anymore, but--

65
00:03:39,486 --> 00:03:43,490
jotaro! He’s catching up to you!

66
00:03:43,524 --> 00:03:45,960
N’doul: I hear
jotaro’s star platinum

67
00:03:45,993 --> 00:03:48,095
is the fiercest
of the enemies’ stands.

68
00:03:48,128 --> 00:03:50,364
Master dio will be
beside himself with joy

69
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:52,499
if I take care of him
here and now.

70
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:54,969
In the name of master dio,

71
00:03:55,002 --> 00:03:58,506
i’ll use every fiber of my being
to finally vanquish jotaro.

72
00:03:58,539 --> 00:04:00,241
( Iggy grumbles, gasps )

73
00:04:03,043 --> 00:04:05,145
( Yelps )

74
00:04:05,179 --> 00:04:07,348
N’doul: Hmm.
If I heard correctly,

75
00:04:07,381 --> 00:04:10,284
jotaro just picked something up
off the sand.

76
00:04:10,317 --> 00:04:13,086
Let’s see.
What was at that location?

77
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,622
Last I checked, it was--

78
00:04:14,655 --> 00:04:16,624
( gasps ) Wait. I remember!

79
00:04:16,657 --> 00:04:20,394
The dog! Jotaro grabbed the dog,
which means he knows!

80
00:04:20,427 --> 00:04:22,296
Jotaro: I’ve finally
figured you out, mutt.

81
00:04:22,329 --> 00:04:25,499
I know you jumped out of the car
before the stand attacked it.

82
00:04:25,532 --> 00:04:27,434
You can smell it, can’t you?

83
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:30,403
You know where it’s gonna be
before it gets there.

84
00:04:32,673 --> 00:04:35,442
Joseph: Gah!
Don’t stop moving, jotaro!

85
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:39,379
Jotaro: Now, iggy, I think it’s
time for you to earn your keep.

86
00:04:39,413 --> 00:04:42,950
Where’s the stand coming from?
Just show me, already.

87
00:04:42,983 --> 00:04:44,551
Show me, or we die,

88
00:04:44,585 --> 00:04:47,188
and how would you
get your gum then?

89
00:04:56,997 --> 00:04:58,232
Joseph: Huh?

90
00:05:01,435 --> 00:05:04,104
( The fool squeals ) Iggy!

91
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:05,138
Jotaro: Iggy!

92
00:05:06,373 --> 00:05:07,975
You’ve gotta be kidding me.

93
00:05:08,008 --> 00:05:10,143
He can fly, too? Not so fast.

94
00:05:10,177 --> 00:05:12,613
( The fool grunts )

95
00:05:14,014 --> 00:05:16,283
Jotaro: Go ahead,
and pant all you want.

96
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:18,485
You’re not
getting out of this one.

97
00:05:18,519 --> 00:05:20,421
Star platinum’s
as fast as they come.

98
00:05:20,454 --> 00:05:22,156
If you’re thinking
of dropping me,

99
00:05:22,189 --> 00:05:24,558
i’ll snap your neck
before you can blink.

100
00:05:24,591 --> 00:05:25,559
( Iggy yelps )

101
00:05:25,592 --> 00:05:27,160
N’doul: What?

102
00:05:27,194 --> 00:05:29,697
It’s like he jumped
and suddenly disappeared.

103
00:05:29,730 --> 00:05:31,432
This is impossible.

104
00:05:31,465 --> 00:05:33,701
They must have landed somewhere.

105
00:05:35,202 --> 00:05:36,704
Joseph: That’s brilliant.

106
00:05:36,737 --> 00:05:40,174
We can’t move around,
so to bypass that handicap,

107
00:05:40,207 --> 00:05:42,710
jotaro’s using iggy
to find the stand user.

108
00:05:42,743 --> 00:05:45,512
If we can find whoever’s
controlling the stand,

109
00:05:45,546 --> 00:05:48,516
we might actually have
a chance of defeating him.

110
00:05:48,549 --> 00:05:49,717
( Bubbling )

111
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,218
N’doul: He’s vanished.

112
00:05:51,251 --> 00:05:53,353
I can’t hear jotaro’s footsteps.

113
00:05:53,387 --> 00:05:55,623
Where is he? Where did he go?

114
00:05:55,656 --> 00:05:57,625
Why can’t I hear his footsteps?

115
00:05:57,658 --> 00:05:59,426
( Iggy panting )

116
00:05:59,459 --> 00:06:01,995
Polnareff: Oh, no.
They’re flying lower and lower.

117
00:06:03,197 --> 00:06:05,232
This isn’t gonna end well.

118
00:06:05,265 --> 00:06:07,601
It looks like the fool
can’t travel long distances.

119
00:06:07,634 --> 00:06:10,937
Joseph: The damn thing is
gliding like a paper airplane!

120
00:06:10,971 --> 00:06:12,105
( Jotaro groans )

121
00:06:12,139 --> 00:06:14,041
My legs are
about to touch the ground.

122
00:06:14,074 --> 00:06:15,676
- ( Iggy farting )
- Jotaro: Hey, mutt,

123
00:06:15,709 --> 00:06:17,411
quit tensing up like that.

124
00:06:17,444 --> 00:06:19,913
You’re starting to fart again.

125
00:06:19,947 --> 00:06:22,383
For your sake, you better
not let out a big one.

126
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:26,020
( Sighs ) No choice.

127
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:28,355
We need to get more air,
and at this point,

128
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:30,123
there’s only one way to do it.

129
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:34,995
Jotaro: Ora!

130
00:06:35,028 --> 00:06:37,531
- ( N’doul gasps )
- ( Iggy howls )

131
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,633
Jotaro: That kick
got us a lot closer

132
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:41,334
to our destination for sure,

133
00:06:41,368 --> 00:06:44,404
but the sound of it definitely
gave away our strategy.

134
00:06:44,438 --> 00:06:46,173
Now the user will know

135
00:06:46,206 --> 00:06:48,108
that we’re flying
to avoid detection.

136
00:06:48,141 --> 00:06:50,977
N’doul: So that’s why
I wasn’t able to locate them.

137
00:06:51,011 --> 00:06:53,614
The dog’s stand
has the ability to fly.

138
00:06:53,647 --> 00:06:55,983
But now I know
what they’re up to.

139
00:06:56,016 --> 00:06:57,518
They’re headed directly for me.

140
00:06:57,551 --> 00:07:01,055
I have to eliminate jotaro
before he gets any closer!

141
00:07:02,689 --> 00:07:04,357
Polnareff: His stand’s
on the move,

142
00:07:04,391 --> 00:07:05,893
and it’s going after jotaro!

143
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:08,095
He figured it out
when jotaro kicked off!

144
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:11,231
Joseph: There’s nothing
we can do about it.

145
00:07:11,265 --> 00:07:15,269
The only thing we can do now
is trust jotaro.

146
00:07:16,303 --> 00:07:17,638
Jotaro: He’s coming.

147
00:07:17,671 --> 00:07:20,240
I know he was able
to bring down a helicopter,

148
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:23,244
but he shouldn’t be able
to find our exact location

149
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:25,246
since iggy’s stand
barely makes a sound.

150
00:07:25,279 --> 00:07:28,015
I just have to get
to the stand user

151
00:07:28,048 --> 00:07:30,284
before landing,
and it’ll be lights out.

152
00:07:38,559 --> 00:07:41,028
There he is.

153
00:07:41,061 --> 00:07:44,364
The stand user’s
about 400 meters away.

154
00:07:48,035 --> 00:07:50,971
And from the looks of things,
our enemy is blind.

155
00:07:51,004 --> 00:07:52,372
( Sand clattering )

156
00:07:53,974 --> 00:07:56,510
Damn it.
Sand’s falling from the sky.

157
00:07:58,212 --> 00:08:01,148
Of course. The stand user
must be trying to find us.

158
00:08:01,181 --> 00:08:03,984
He’s using the sand
bouncing off the wings

159
00:08:04,017 --> 00:08:05,919
like a submarine uses sonar.

160
00:08:05,953 --> 00:08:07,321
♪

161
00:08:07,354 --> 00:08:08,922
( N’doul chuckles )

162
00:08:08,956 --> 00:08:11,926
Because of the falling sand,
I can hear you now.

163
00:08:16,063 --> 00:08:20,701
And i’ve discovered
your exact location, jotaro!

164
00:08:23,537 --> 00:08:25,406
( Jotaro groans )

165
00:08:30,043 --> 00:08:31,411
N’doul: Time to die!

166
00:08:31,445 --> 00:08:33,580
Jotaro: Star platinum!

167
00:08:33,614 --> 00:08:36,150
Star platinum: Ora!

168
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:38,118
- ( Iggy yelps )
- ( N’doul laughs )

169
00:08:38,151 --> 00:08:40,987
Star platinum’s speed won’t
be of much use, i’m afraid!

170
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:43,524
If you can’t tell where
my attack is coming from,

171
00:08:43,557 --> 00:08:45,225
then my stand has the advantage!

172
00:08:45,259 --> 00:08:47,228
( Jotaro gasps )

173
00:08:47,261 --> 00:08:48,229
( N’doul laughs )

174
00:08:48,262 --> 00:08:49,864
Here comes another!

175
00:08:49,897 --> 00:08:51,465
( Iggy groans )

176
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,135
Iggy: Iggy.

177
00:08:55,169 --> 00:08:57,138
Iggy.

178
00:08:59,606 --> 00:09:00,941
- ( Iggy groans )
- Jotaro: Shit.

179
00:09:00,974 --> 00:09:02,342
You damn mutt!

180
00:09:02,376 --> 00:09:04,245
( N’doul laughs )

181
00:09:04,278 --> 00:09:07,915
What a dog! He’s dragging jotaro
right into my trap!

182
00:09:07,948 --> 00:09:11,351
It seems like he’ll do anything
to save his own hide! ( Laughs )

183
00:09:11,385 --> 00:09:13,988
Even abandon his master!

184
00:09:14,021 --> 00:09:16,323
( Laughs )

185
00:09:16,356 --> 00:09:17,357
Jotaro: Bastard.

186
00:09:17,391 --> 00:09:19,360
Just you wait.

187
00:09:19,393 --> 00:09:21,095
N’doul: That’s what you get

188
00:09:21,128 --> 00:09:24,164
for relying on such
a fickle creature, jotaro.

189
00:09:24,198 --> 00:09:26,534
Your end has come,

190
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:28,836
and now it’s finally time

191
00:09:28,869 --> 00:09:31,071
to put you out of your misery.

192
00:09:33,407 --> 00:09:35,576
( Iggy yelps )

193
00:09:35,609 --> 00:09:38,579
Star platinum: O...

194
00:09:39,613 --> 00:09:41,281
Jotaro: Ora!

195
00:09:41,315 --> 00:09:42,483
( Iggy howls )

196
00:09:42,516 --> 00:09:44,451
( N’doul gasps ) What’s this?

197
00:09:44,484 --> 00:09:46,519
It feels like he
just threw something at me!

198
00:09:46,553 --> 00:09:49,523
I can’t make out
what it is at that speed.

199
00:09:49,556 --> 00:09:52,559
Jotaro: I tossed iggy at you.
Get a move on.

200
00:09:52,593 --> 00:09:54,995
You’d better use your stand
to defend yourselves,

201
00:09:55,028 --> 00:09:56,930
or else you two
are gonna be closer

202
00:09:56,964 --> 00:09:58,332
than you ever wanted to be.

203
00:09:58,365 --> 00:10:00,167
N’doul: Such insane velocity.

204
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,334
( Iggy squealing )

205
00:10:03,170 --> 00:10:05,039
N’doul: Damn it!
It’s going to hit me!

206
00:10:11,378 --> 00:10:12,913
I can’t believe it.

207
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:15,215
He actually threw the dog.

208
00:10:15,249 --> 00:10:17,284
( Groans ) Blast it!
I was so close

209
00:10:17,317 --> 00:10:20,053
to putting an end
to that wretch once and for all.

210
00:10:20,087 --> 00:10:21,989
Huh?

211
00:10:22,990 --> 00:10:24,492
( Iggy panting )

212
00:10:24,525 --> 00:10:28,229
N’doul: No. I was so busy
worrying about that damn dog,

213
00:10:28,262 --> 00:10:30,598
I completely lost
jotaro’s location.

214
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:34,335
Where? Where is he?

215
00:10:34,368 --> 00:10:37,004
♪

216
00:10:37,037 --> 00:10:38,405
It’s like he vanished,

217
00:10:38,438 --> 00:10:41,141
and he’s
staying absolutely still.

218
00:10:41,175 --> 00:10:43,911
That must have been his plan.

219
00:10:43,944 --> 00:10:46,280
Where the hell are you?

220
00:10:46,313 --> 00:10:48,248
You can’t hide forever.

221
00:10:48,282 --> 00:10:51,986
Show yourself, jotaro!

222
00:10:52,019 --> 00:10:54,054
♪

223
00:10:55,022 --> 00:10:56,090
Jotaro: I’m right here.

224
00:11:03,096 --> 00:11:04,130
( N’doul gasps )

225
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,868
( Iggy yelps )

226
00:11:07,901 --> 00:11:10,537
N’doul: I see.

227
00:11:10,571 --> 00:11:13,541
I didn’t realize
you’d slink so close.

228
00:11:13,574 --> 00:11:15,543
If I hadn’t had the foresight

229
00:11:15,576 --> 00:11:17,912
to protect myself
with this water shield,

230
00:11:17,945 --> 00:11:20,314
you would have already
knocked me out from behind.

231
00:11:20,347 --> 00:11:22,182
I suppose
I should count myself lucky

232
00:11:22,216 --> 00:11:24,185
it makes
for such a good defense.

233
00:11:24,218 --> 00:11:26,987
Given that we’re now
in such close proximity,

234
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:29,990
I no longer need this cane
to hear you.

235
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:34,961
However, I will require its use
when I return home.

236
00:11:34,995 --> 00:11:36,997
♪

237
00:11:46,607 --> 00:11:48,209
Iggy: Iggy. Iggy.

238
00:11:53,447 --> 00:11:55,282
Iggy.

239
00:11:59,887 --> 00:12:01,655
Iggy. Iggy. Iggy.

240
00:12:03,957 --> 00:12:05,192
Iggy!

241
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:06,426
♪

242
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:08,162
Star platinum: Ora!

243
00:12:10,264 --> 00:12:12,233
( N’doul gags )

244
00:12:18,906 --> 00:12:21,175
( Star platinum roars )

245
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:29,182
( N’doul groaning )

246
00:12:29,216 --> 00:12:30,217
( Coughs )

247
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,152
Jotaro: It’s hard to believe,

248
00:12:32,186 --> 00:12:35,056
but you actually managed
to knock off my hat.

249
00:12:35,088 --> 00:12:37,958
You can relax a little.
I was holding back.

250
00:12:37,991 --> 00:12:40,260
You’re not going to die.

251
00:12:41,261 --> 00:12:42,262
( N’doul chuckles )

252
00:12:44,364 --> 00:12:45,565
Jotaro: What the?!

253
00:12:45,599 --> 00:12:47,568
Why the hell would you
use your stand to--

254
00:12:47,601 --> 00:12:50,003
explain. Why did you do it?!

255
00:12:50,037 --> 00:12:51,272
( N’doul groans )

256
00:12:51,305 --> 00:12:52,973
Jotaro...

257
00:12:53,006 --> 00:12:54,641
You--you thought you could--

258
00:12:54,675 --> 00:12:56,577
you thought
you could manipulate me

259
00:12:56,610 --> 00:12:58,979
and force me
to tell you information

260
00:12:59,012 --> 00:13:01,515
regarding the other eight
stand users, didn’t you?

261
00:13:01,548 --> 00:13:04,518
( Groans )
I’m very well aware...

262
00:13:04,551 --> 00:13:07,421
That Joseph joestar’s
hermit purple...

263
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:09,456
Can view
into the minds of others.

264
00:13:09,489 --> 00:13:10,523
( Groans )

265
00:13:10,557 --> 00:13:12,859
You’ll never get inside my head,

266
00:13:12,893 --> 00:13:14,395
and i’ll never tell you

267
00:13:14,428 --> 00:13:17,364
anything that you could use
against my master.

268
00:13:17,397 --> 00:13:18,365
( Laughs )

269
00:13:18,398 --> 00:13:20,000
Jotaro: Dio.

270
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:22,969
I don’t understand why
you’re so loyal to him.

271
00:13:23,003 --> 00:13:26,540
Are you honestly telling me
that you’d die for him?

272
00:13:26,573 --> 00:13:29,176
N’doul: Jotaro, you’re right.

273
00:13:29,209 --> 00:13:30,410
You don’t understand.

274
00:13:30,444 --> 00:13:33,414
Fear of death
holds no place in my heart.

275
00:13:33,447 --> 00:13:35,349
( Laughs )

276
00:13:35,382 --> 00:13:37,618
Because of the power
of my stand,

277
00:13:37,651 --> 00:13:40,621
i’ve always been able
to live a life unencumbered

278
00:13:40,654 --> 00:13:43,457
by such inconsequential fears
like death.

279
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:46,326
I could always win any fight.

280
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:50,130
I could have and do
whatever I wanted.

281
00:13:50,164 --> 00:13:53,501
Killing and stealing were
absolutely meaningless to me.

282
00:13:53,534 --> 00:13:56,437
You should talk
to the mutt about it.

283
00:13:56,470 --> 00:13:59,139
I’m sure he knows how I feel.

284
00:13:59,173 --> 00:14:00,975
Dio was the first person

285
00:14:01,008 --> 00:14:05,045
who was able to look deep within
my soul and find something more.

286
00:14:05,078 --> 00:14:08,515
He was the one
who gave me a desire to live.

287
00:14:08,549 --> 00:14:11,419
That glorious force of nature...

288
00:14:11,451 --> 00:14:15,922
He was so strong,
so wise, so beautiful.

289
00:14:15,956 --> 00:14:19,193
He was the one and only
person in my life

290
00:14:19,226 --> 00:14:21,962
to ever see a purpose
for my existence.

291
00:14:21,995 --> 00:14:24,231
( Gasps )

292
00:14:24,264 --> 00:14:29,603
I waited such a long time
for an opportunity to meet him.

293
00:14:31,071 --> 00:14:33,540
I will gladly die
for my master’s sake.

294
00:14:33,574 --> 00:14:35,476
( Coughs ) But no matter what,

295
00:14:35,509 --> 00:14:38,078
I refuse to do anything
that would disappoint him.

296
00:14:38,111 --> 00:14:39,379
( Coughs )

297
00:14:39,413 --> 00:14:42,483
And after all, evil or not,

298
00:14:42,516 --> 00:14:45,019
a scoundrel needs someone
to put his faith in.

299
00:14:45,052 --> 00:14:47,087
( Laughs )

300
00:14:48,155 --> 00:14:50,658
I’ll tell you this before I go.

301
00:14:50,691 --> 00:14:53,460
You should know
that my name is n’doul,

302
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:57,497
and my stand hails from Egypt,
the birthplace of the tarot.

303
00:14:57,531 --> 00:15:00,401
It’s referred to as one
of the nine gods of Egypt,

304
00:15:00,434 --> 00:15:02,369
geb of the great ennead.

305
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:06,273
We call it
the god of the earth.

306
00:15:06,306 --> 00:15:07,841
Jotaro: Nine Egyptian gods?

307
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:09,176
What does that mean?!

308
00:15:09,209 --> 00:15:10,544
( N’doul laughs )

309
00:15:10,577 --> 00:15:13,847
Sorry, but i’ll only
tell you about my stand.

310
00:15:13,881 --> 00:15:15,282
It’s only fair,

311
00:15:15,315 --> 00:15:17,984
since you’re the one
who ended up stopping me.

312
00:15:18,018 --> 00:15:21,188
But info on my compatriots
goes with me to my grave.

313
00:15:21,221 --> 00:15:24,057
♪

314
00:15:39,473 --> 00:15:41,475
( Footsteps crunching )

315
00:15:55,055 --> 00:15:58,392
Jotaro: Dio brainwashes people
like a cult leader.

316
00:15:58,425 --> 00:16:01,161
Just who is this guy, exactly?

317
00:16:01,195 --> 00:16:04,432
And what’s this crap
about the nine gods of Egypt?

318
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:05,999
It’s all a mystery...

319
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:09,303
But for now, we just
have to keep moving forward.

320
00:16:12,339 --> 00:16:13,907
( Iggy growls )

321
00:16:13,941 --> 00:16:16,110
Jotaro: Hey, you don’t
have to be defensive.

322
00:16:16,143 --> 00:16:18,445
It’s not like i’m angry
with you or anything.

323
00:16:18,478 --> 00:16:20,080
Makes sense you’d be pissed.

324
00:16:20,113 --> 00:16:22,616
I doubt you wanted to be
dragged out into the desert

325
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:24,451
and forced
into some human crap.

326
00:16:24,484 --> 00:16:26,519
Your position must suck ass.

327
00:16:26,553 --> 00:16:28,622
No one can blame you
for being upset.

328
00:16:29,656 --> 00:16:31,591
Iggy, here. You want some gum?

329
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:33,660
( Iggy growling )

330
00:16:35,662 --> 00:16:37,631
Jotaro: Would you
calm down already?

331
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:39,199
I’m trying to apologize.

332
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:40,568
Take it.

333
00:16:40,601 --> 00:16:42,103
( Iggy barks )

334
00:16:42,135 --> 00:16:43,436
Jotaro: Good grief.

335
00:16:43,470 --> 00:16:45,605
That dog is a pain in the ass.

336
00:16:45,639 --> 00:16:48,909
You can stay out here
in the desert for all I care.

337
00:16:50,477 --> 00:16:52,312
- Iggy: Iggy.
- Jotaro: Hmm?

338
00:16:52,346 --> 00:16:55,249
( Iggy whimpering )

339
00:16:55,282 --> 00:16:57,317
Jotaro: Huh.
Well, what do you know?

340
00:16:57,351 --> 00:17:00,187
You went back
and fetched my hat for me.

341
00:17:03,023 --> 00:17:05,826
Maybe you’re
not so bad after all.

342
00:17:05,859 --> 00:17:07,060
Thanks.

343
00:17:08,095 --> 00:17:10,431
( Squish )

344
00:17:11,431 --> 00:17:12,432
( Iggy chuckles )

345
00:17:14,301 --> 00:17:16,336
Jotaro: You put gum in here?

346
00:17:16,370 --> 00:17:18,539
You good-for-nothing, little--

347
00:17:18,572 --> 00:17:20,340
you’re no ordinary mutt.

348
00:17:20,374 --> 00:17:21,542
Joseph: Hey!

349
00:17:21,575 --> 00:17:23,544
Jotaro!

350
00:17:23,577 --> 00:17:25,546
- Jotaro: Huh?
- Polnareff: Jotaro!

351
00:17:25,579 --> 00:17:27,114
Are you all right?

352
00:17:27,147 --> 00:17:28,548
( Iggy howls )

353
00:17:28,582 --> 00:17:30,117
( Barking )

354
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:31,151
( Jotaro sighs )

355
00:17:33,253 --> 00:17:34,554
Good grief.

356
00:17:35,556 --> 00:17:37,558
♪

357
00:19:05,212 --> 00:19:07,648
♪

358
00:19:10,717 --> 00:19:12,686
Man: Ah, sweet! Hey, there.

359
00:19:12,719 --> 00:19:14,487
Is that a comic book
you’re readin’, little man?

360
00:19:14,521 --> 00:19:15,956
I’ve never seen one here.

361
00:19:15,989 --> 00:19:18,725
So Egyptians read comics
just like the rest of us.

362
00:19:18,759 --> 00:19:20,928
You want some mini doughnuts?

363
00:19:23,096 --> 00:19:24,898
Hey, mind if I see
your comic book?

364
00:19:24,932 --> 00:19:27,501
If you’ll let me, I promise
i’ll be super careful with it.

365
00:19:27,534 --> 00:19:30,170
I’m a comic book artist
who’s searching for inspiration.

366
00:19:30,204 --> 00:19:31,772
Nothing gets me jazzed up more

367
00:19:31,805 --> 00:19:33,607
than checking out
rare books and comics.

368
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:36,510
Let me borrow it,
and you can use my binoculars.

369
00:19:36,543 --> 00:19:37,511
Boy: Hmm?

370
00:19:37,544 --> 00:19:39,813
Artist: What the? How peculiar.

371
00:19:39,847 --> 00:19:42,817
The story’s about these
two eerie-looking brothers?

372
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:46,053
I don’t see the creator’s name.

373
00:19:46,086 --> 00:19:47,254
Wow!

374
00:19:47,287 --> 00:19:49,990
These are all
such bizarre drawings.

375
00:19:50,023 --> 00:19:51,825
But this is fantastic
print quality,

376
00:19:51,859 --> 00:19:53,260
not to mention
it’s in full color!

377
00:19:53,293 --> 00:19:55,495
Boy: "There once
lived two brothers

378
00:19:55,529 --> 00:19:57,798
who got along very well."

379
00:19:57,831 --> 00:19:59,266
Man #2:
"’my name is zenyatta.’"

380
00:19:59,299 --> 00:20:01,101
boy: "’my name is mondatta.’

381
00:20:01,134 --> 00:20:04,104
"mondatta, the younger brother,
was very shy

382
00:20:04,137 --> 00:20:06,940
"and wouldn’t do anything
unless zenyatta was with him.

383
00:20:06,974 --> 00:20:08,108
"He was always alone.

384
00:20:09,710 --> 00:20:12,913
"One day, while his big brother
zenyatta was away,

385
00:20:12,946 --> 00:20:16,049
"mondatta met a kind traveler
near the side of the road.

386
00:20:16,083 --> 00:20:20,154
"He gave mondatta yummy snacks
and let him use his binoculars.

387
00:20:20,187 --> 00:20:23,090
Mondatta had more fun
than he’d had in a long time."

388
00:20:23,123 --> 00:20:25,025
Artist: "’oh, it’s 10:30!’"

389
00:20:25,058 --> 00:20:28,562
boy: "But unfortunately
the very kind traveler

390
00:20:28,595 --> 00:20:32,866
was impaled on a telephone pole
and died a horrific death."

391
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:35,603
Artist: Quite a weird comic
you’ve got.

392
00:20:35,636 --> 00:20:38,205
Is this comic especially popular
in this place?

393
00:20:38,238 --> 00:20:40,674
If you ask me,
it’s really strange.

394
00:20:40,707 --> 00:20:43,210
The other pages are all blank.

395
00:20:43,243 --> 00:20:45,746
It’s like they forgot
to print the rest.

396
00:20:45,779 --> 00:20:46,980
Must be a dud.

397
00:20:48,615 --> 00:20:51,651
But somehow I feel as though
I have a connection to it.

398
00:20:51,685 --> 00:20:52,920
It’s totally pulled me in.

399
00:20:52,953 --> 00:20:54,621
This is gonna sound crazy,

400
00:20:54,655 --> 00:20:57,191
but would it be possible for me
to buy this book from you?

401
00:20:57,224 --> 00:20:58,792
- Man: It’s not for sale!
- Artist: Huh?

402
00:20:58,825 --> 00:21:00,160
Man: Are you deaf or somethin’?

403
00:21:00,194 --> 00:21:02,596
My bro’s book’s not for sale!

404
00:21:02,629 --> 00:21:04,598
Now get out of my sight.

405
00:21:04,631 --> 00:21:06,099
Artist: This kid
is your brother?

406
00:21:06,133 --> 00:21:08,102
Man: I won’t tell you again!

407
00:21:08,135 --> 00:21:10,170
( Artist wails )

408
00:21:11,905 --> 00:21:15,041
Man: Hey, what have I told you
about talking to strangers?

409
00:21:15,075 --> 00:21:16,610
There’s lots of bad people

410
00:21:16,643 --> 00:21:18,545
roaming the world these days,
you know?

411
00:21:18,579 --> 00:21:19,947
Conductor: Last call!

412
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:22,950
The bus for aswan
is getting ready to depart!

413
00:21:22,983 --> 00:21:24,585
Man: That’s us.

414
00:21:24,618 --> 00:21:26,954
They’re on their way
to the hospital in aswan

415
00:21:26,987 --> 00:21:29,957
to drop off their friend
and have his injuries treated.

416
00:21:29,990 --> 00:21:32,059
Hmm?

417
00:21:32,092 --> 00:21:34,661
Ah. You don’t say?

418
00:21:34,695 --> 00:21:36,197
If that’s how it is,

419
00:21:36,230 --> 00:21:39,233
we’ll just have to wait
for the next bus.

420
00:21:43,003 --> 00:21:45,172
( Sirens blaring )

421
00:21:45,205 --> 00:21:47,174
♪

422
00:21:47,207 --> 00:21:49,643
( Passengers murmuring )

